  <!-- TRV SECTION -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Thermostatic Radiator Valves for Liverpool Homes</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">A TRV on every radiator is one of the most cost-effective heating improvements available for a Liverpool home. Required on all new installations under Boiler Plus regulations.</p>

      <div style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-pros">
          <h3 style="text-align:center;">Why Every Liverpool Radiator Should Have a TRV</h3>
          <ul class="pf-check-list">
            <li>Controls heat output room by room. The sitting room runs warmer, the spare bedroom cooler. No heat wasted in rooms that do not need it</li>
            <li>Reduces heating bills by 10 to 15%. The <a href="https://energysavingtrust.org.uk/advice/thermostats-and-heating-controls/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Energy Saving Trust</a> estimates TRVs in a typical Liverpool semi can save up to £75 per year on heating bills</li>
            <li>Required under <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/boiler-plus" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boiler Plus regulations</a> on all new radiator installations from 2018</li>
            <li>Prevents overheating in rooms with solar gain. South-facing Liverpool living rooms stay comfortable without wasting gas</li>
            <li>Compatible with all modern boilers and smart thermostat systems</li>
            <li>Fitted from £50 per valve. A full house of TRV upgrades typically costs £150 to £300 and pays for itself within two heating seasons</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-info-bar" style="margin-top:2rem;">
          <p style="font-size:0.88rem;color:var(--text);">Note: one radiator in the house (usually the hallway) should be left without a TRV to act as a bypass. This allows the boiler to circulate water even when all other TRVs are closed. We always advise on this when fitting TRVs across a full property.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- VICTORIAN PROPERTIES -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Radiator Installation in Liverpool's Victorian Properties</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Liverpool's Victorian and Edwardian housing stock presents specific challenges for radiator installation. Our engineers have 30 years experience with every type of Liverpool property.</p>

      <div class="pf-card pf-card-navy" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <h3>Solid Walls, Suspended Floors and Period Features</h3>
        <p>Victorian terraces in Aigburth, Allerton, Anfield, Toxteth, Wavertree and across the city have solid brick walls rather than cavity walls. Horizontal pipe runs across solid walls must be either surface-mounted in boxing or run under suspended timber floors where access allows. Both approaches are workable. We assess each room at the quote visit and advise on the neatest route for your specific property.</p>
        <p>Suspended timber floors in Liverpool's Victorian properties usually allow pipes to be run below without disturbing floor coverings in the rooms above. Where floors are solid concrete, surface-mounted pipework in neat boxing is the standard approach. We plan every pipe route to minimise visual impact on period features including coving, picture rails and original skirting boards.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pf-card pf-card-orange" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <h3>Choosing the Right Radiator Style for a Period Liverpool Property</h3>
        <p>Standard double panel radiators work perfectly well in period properties and deliver more heat for their price than column alternatives. If aesthetics are important, column radiators in traditional two or four column configurations complement Victorian interiors well and are available in heights up to 1800mm for rooms with high ceilings.</p>
        <p>For Liverpool properties with large bay window alcoves, a radiator positioned in the bay is the most effective way to counteract cold air from the window. We size bay radiators correctly for the room rather than fitting whatever fits the alcove. Undersized bay radiators are one of the most common causes of cold front rooms in Liverpool Victorian terraces.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- POWER FLUSH LINK -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Should You Power Flush Before Fitting New Radiators?</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">If your existing system has sludge build-up, fitting new radiators to a contaminated circuit will fill them quickly. Here is how to know if you need a flush first.</p>

      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>You need a power flush first if...</strong><p>Multiple existing radiators have cold spots at the bottom. The water that comes out when you bleed radiators is brown or black. Your boiler makes banging or kettling sounds. The system takes a long time to warm up. Any of these indicate sludge in the circuit that will contaminate new radiators immediately.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid var(--green);"><span class="pf-who-icon" style="color:var(--green);">✓</span><div><strong>You do not need a flush if...</strong><p>Your existing radiators all heat evenly, the system warms up quickly, and the water from bleeding is clear. In this case new radiators can be connected directly to the circuit with a top-up of inhibitor on completion.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>We advise at the quote visit</strong><p>We assess the condition of your system when we visit to quote for the radiator work. If a power flush is recommended, we will tell you and explain why. We never recommend work that is not necessary. A power flush costs from £350 and can be combined with radiator work at a better overall price.</p></div></div>
      </div>

      <div style="text-align:center;margin-top:2rem;">
        <a href="/power-flushing-liverpool" class="btn btn-navy btn-lg" style="color:#ffffff;">Learn About Power Flushing</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY CHOOSE -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why Over 250 Liverpool Homeowners Choose Ideal Plumbing for Radiator Work</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Fixed prices. Our own Gas Safe engineers. System balanced on completion. All Liverpool postcodes covered.</p>
      <div class="pf-why-grid">
        <div class="pf-why-item"><h3>Fixed Price Before We Start</h3><p>We quote the job before any work begins. The price we quote is the price on the invoice. No additions on the day, no surprises after the work is done.</p></div>
        <div class="pf-why-item"><h3>System Balanced on Completion</h3><p>Every radiator installation includes a system balance on completion. This is often skipped by cheaper operators. Without balancing, newly fitted radiators can starve other radiators of heat and cause uneven temperatures throughout the house.</p></div>
        <div class="pf-why-item"><h3>Our Own Gas Safe Engineers</h3><p>All radiator work connecting to the heating circuit is carried out by our own directly employed Gas Safe registered engineers. Never a sub-contractor.</p></div>
