  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Radiators Liverpool. Your Questions Answered</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Straight answers to what Liverpool homeowners ask most before booking.</p>
      <div class="pf-faq">
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does radiator installation cost in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A standard double panel radiator supply and fit costs from £200, including the radiator, TRV and system balance. Labour only for a like-for-like replacement starts from £80. TRV upgrades from £50 per valve. Radiator relocation from £150. Column and designer radiators are priced on quotation. We provide a written fixed-price quote before any work begins.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">TIME</span>&nbsp; How long does radiator installation take?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A like-for-like single radiator replacement takes 1 to 2 hours. A new radiator addition including new pipework takes 2 to 4 hours. Multiple radiators can often be completed in a single day. A full house TRV upgrade typically takes half a day. We confirm the expected duration when we provide the quote.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">TRV</span>&nbsp; What is a TRV and do I need one?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A thermostatic radiator valve controls the heat output of an individual radiator, allowing different temperatures in different rooms. Under <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/boiler-plus" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boiler Plus regulations</a>, TRVs are required on all new radiator installations. They reduce heating bills by 10 to 15%. We fit TRVs from £50 per valve. One radiator in the house should be left without a TRV to act as a bypass. We always advise on this.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">FLUSH</span>&nbsp; Do I need a power flush before fitting new radiators?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>If your existing radiators have cold spots at the bottom or the system water is brown or black when bled, a power flush is strongly recommended before fitting new radiators. A contaminated circuit will fill new radiators with sludge quickly. We assess the system condition at the quote visit and advise honestly on whether a flush is needed.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">VICTORIAN</span>&nbsp; Can you relocate a radiator in a Liverpool Victorian property?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. We drain down the circuit, reroute the pipework to the new position and rebalance the system. Relocation starts from £150 depending on distance and pipework complexity. In Liverpool's Victorian terraces with solid walls, pipework is usually run under suspended timber floors or surface-mounted in neat boxing.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">GAS SAFE</span>&nbsp; Are you Gas Safe registered?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Ideal Plumbing Solutions is Gas Safe registered. All radiator work connecting to the heating circuit is carried out by our own directly employed Gas Safe registered engineers. Verify at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. We never use sub-contractors.</p></div></details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

